1. INTRODUCTION
----------------
filterBAM is a C++ routine based on filterPSL, a Perl script written by Prof. Dr. Mario Stanke for the 
cleaning of PSL alignment files. See more on the accompanying PDF file.

2. INSTALLATION
----------------
Type in the command line

> make

Executable binary file should be stored in the folder "bin", under the name "filterBam", i.e.

> cd bin
>./filterBam --help

3. RUNNING
----------------




